Description: Sellers: We sell homes differently and here is a small taste of what we do, but to see for yourself go to MoreThanAFloorPlan.com. While in search of his first apartment at DePaul University, John noticed a lack of resources and support for students. While still a student, he began his business plan for Renters Refuge, Chicago's first student-focused and student-owned real estate brokerage. Two years after incorporating Renters Refuge, John was honored by a mention in the WSJ. Shortly there after, Prudential Rubloff, acquired Renters Refuge and his career selling New Construction and Luxury Homes began.New Construction and Luxury Homes have been specialties of John's from the start. Before the age of 23, his experience working in construction and being involved in over 50 property flips, holds, and developments has created a strong foundation for advising clients purchasing any home, especially new construction, and creating marketing and sales strategies when representing sellers and developers.Meet the Business Owner

Buy and sell Chicago homes, lofts or condos in Chicago neighborhoods with the best real estate agents.HistoryEstablished in 1998.When we first opened our doors, Dream Town had a tiny office--two desks pushed together, a phone, an espresso machine, and a promise. We had just enough to keep the lights on and the coffee brewing. That espresso machine, filled with exquisite, dark roast coffee, naturally became the center of our office.Gathering together, mugs in hand--we chatted and sipped. Comparing notes and swapping stories, we bonded. Sharing coffee, we listened and looked after one another.Our office was so small then, that our clients became part of our inner circle. Sometimes, they even stopped by just to have a cup of coffee. They told us what was important to them, and we came together as advisors and friends.Nine espresso machines later, we're entering into our third office and our clients continue to be part of our close family. Still sharing our coffee, we haven't lost sight of those little things that made us successful.

Name: Artizen Realty
Description: Artizen Realty is local, minority-owned and committed to eco-friendly business practices. We are a full service residential brokerage specializing in first-time & investment buyer …Learn more about Artizen Realty, Opens a popupSpecialtiesArtizen Realty is local, minority-owned and committed to eco-friendly business practices. We are a full service residential brokerage specializing in first-time & investment buyer representation, estate sales and property management. Though the company frequently deals with all other aspects of real estate, each agent has unique credentials that lean them toward certain specialties. For example, one agent is also a licensed home inspector and another has a degree in construction management. For buyers, this means that they are informed about the home, literally from the inside out, before proceeding with a formal home inspection. There are few surprises when you have this knowledge ahead of time! For our sellers, by finding problems before listing and before the buyer has an inspection, we can make recommendations for repairs so that the deal proceeds smoothly. For landlords, we are not merely middle men. We have the legal ability to do diagnostic troubleshooting, something usually hired out to third parties. This saves the landlord time and money. We prefer to get our hands dirty...if we can fix the problem ourselves, we will!All active agents at Artizen Realty have additional qualifications like this. We primarily service Chicago, the west and northwest suburbs. We invite you to call our office to discuss your situation and to determine who can serve you best.HistoryEstablished in 2010.Artizen Realty was founded by Maximilian Ortega in February of 2010 after being a top producer at the nation's largest independent real estate brokerage for 3 years. The traditional way of transacting real estate was slow, outdated, inefficient, and environmentally destructive (this was highlighted during an NBC video segment back in 2010). We created our own systems to transact real estate in a eco-friendly and paperless way. Within one year, our clients had the ability to purchase real estate through an iPhone and without using paper (or commercial "digital signature" products). Today we continue to find ways to make the real estate purchase/sale process more streamlined. Our expertise has expanded beyond purchasing and selling and into the technical fields related to real estate. Going forward, our agents will continue to distinguish themselves by holding other licenses and degrees directly related to their real estate fields.Meet the Business Owner

Description: Gary Lucido is the Team Lead of Lucid Realty who is a full service, discount real estate brokerage offering discount commissions to sellers and rebates to buyers. Lucid Realty, …Learn more about Lucid Realty, Opens a popupSpecialtiesGary Lucido is the Team Lead of Lucid Realty who is a full service, discount real estate brokerage offering discount commissions to sellers and rebates to buyers. Lucid Realty, distances itself from traditional brokerages and provides a better value to the consumer:* It is a full service broker,* Offering substantial savings to both buyers and sellers,* Providing services by employees not independent contractors,* Working as a team instead of competing against one another,* With professionalism and high standards of customer service.Our discounted commission and buyer rebates are based on a sliding scale, the higher the price, the more you save!HistoryEstablished in 2008.Established in 2008For years Gary Lucido had been perplexed by the residential real estate brokerage business. Many of the agents he had encountered over the years just weren't that impressive and the commissions were exorbitant. It was no surprise that the FTC had investigated the industry for anti-competitive practices going back to 1995. It just didn't seem right to have to pay 6% to an agent who was little more than an order taker and didn't do that much to sell your house. After several years, Gary decided to get to the bottom of the mystery himself. So he spent the next few months reading industry studies, reading articles, talking to industry insiders,studying the competition, and reading economic studies. In the end his conclusions surprised him. A good real estate agent really could provide real value. The problem was that there just weren't that many good agents.Meet the Business Owner

After years of getting to know how everything worked over time, I've come to excel at it. With my growing experience came confidence. I am now an annual "Top Producer" which only the top 5% of brokers are designated with in the city.After all my years in the business, I have found a solid balance between my work and my personal life. So many forgo their personal happiness to make a dollar, but that is NOT me. I always will have a smile on my face because I've learned that "quality" is more important than "quantity". As you can see from my amazing clients that have reviewed me here, I am not too bad at what I do! ;)-TedMeet the Business Owner

Description: PERL Mortgage is one of Chicago's TOP correspondent lenders, offering flexible financing options, seamless loan execution, and unparalleled customer support.A question that may …Learn more about Amir Syed - Perl Mortgage, Opens a popupSpecialtiesPERL Mortgage is one of Chicago's TOP correspondent lenders, offering flexible financing options, seamless loan execution, and unparalleled customer support.A question that may come to mind when hearing that:"Correspondent lender, what does that mean and how will it benefit me?" WELL - we streamline the mortgage process by keeping loans in-house from application to closing to ensure speedy turnaround times and incomparable customer service. We employ an open loan process, giving you complete information regarding fees and interest rates up front, eliminating any closing surprises.PERL has maintained a high-level of integrity and superior business practice with a legacy of leadership for nearly 15 years. We've been recognized as an industry leader by Crains Chicago Business, National Mortgage News, Mortgage Originator Magazine and most recently by the Illinois Association of Mortgage Professionals.HistoryEstablished in 1994.PERL Mortgage has been leading Chicago's mortgage industry since 1994, managing loans from application to closing, and is licensed to provide services across the country.Founded by renowned financial authority Ken Perlmutter, PERL is celebrating its second decade as one of Chicago's most respected independent financial institutions - and has three Chicagoland offices with over 100 employees and affiliates across the country.A Timeline of Success2003 - PERL funded $1.1 billion in loans and was named #14 on the prestigious Crain's Chicago Business List of Largest Mortgage Lenders. 2006 - National Mortgage News listed PERL as the top private correspondent lender in Illinois.2009 - PERL was nominated "2008 banker/broker of the Year" by the IL Association of Mortgage Professionals2011 - PERL was ranked #46 Mortgage Co. in the country, according to "Top 100 Mortgage Companies in America 2011"- Mortgage Executive MagazineAnd we're still growing.Meet the Manager
